  "prompt": "What is the weather in orlando like in January?",
  "response": "In Orlando, Florida, the weather in January is typically mild and pleasant. Here are some key points about the weather during this time:\n\n- **Temperature**: \n  - Average high temperatures range from about 70\u00b0F (21\u00b0C) to 75\u00b0F (24\u00b0C).\n  - Average low temperatures typically fall between 50\u00b0F (10\u00b0C) and 55\u00b0F (13\u00b0C).\n\n- **Precipitation**: \n  - January is one of the drier months in Orlando, with an average rainfall of about 2.3 inches (58 mm).\n  - While rain is possible, it usually comes in short bursts rather than prolonged periods.\n\n- **Humidity**: \n  - Humidity levels can be moderate to high, often ranging from 70% to 80%.\n\n- **Sunlight**: \n  - Orlando enjoys plenty of sunshine in January, with an average of 7 to 8 hours of sunlight per day.\n\n- **Clothing Recommendations**: \n  - Light to medium clothing is suitable for the day, but you might want a light jacket or sweater for the cooler evenings.\n\nOverall, January in Orlando offers comfortable weather, making it a great time to visit if you prefer milder temperatures and fewer crowds compared to the peak summer months.",
